  <text xml:lang="ta">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="MM2-intro">iraṇṭāvatu ūralaruraittapāṭṭu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">The second song, in which gossip in the city is reported.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p type="edition"/>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="MM2">
          <l>nāva lōṅkiya māperun tīviṉuṭ</l>
          <l>kāvaṟ teyvatan tēvarkōṟ keṭutta</l>
          <l>tīvakac cānti ceytaru naṉṉāṇ</l>
          <l>maṇimē kalaiyoṭu mātavi vārāt</l>
          <l>taṇiyāt tuṉpan talaittalai mēlvarac</l>
          <l>cittirā patitāṉ cellaluṟ ṟiraṅkit</l>
          <l>tattari neṭuṅkaṭ taṉmaka ṭōḻi</l>
          <l>vayanta mālaiyai varukeṉak kūuyp</l>
          <l>payaṅkeḻu mānaka ralareṭut turaiyeṉa</l>
<l>          vayanta mālaiyu mātavi tuṟavik</l>
<l>kayarntumey vāṭiya vaḻiviṉa ḷātaliṉ</l>
<l>maṇimē kalaiyoṭu mātavi yirunta</l>
<l>vaṇimalar maṇṭapat takavayiṟ celīi</l>
<l>yāṭiya cāya lāyiḻai maṭantai</l>
<l>vāṭiya mēṉi kaṇṭuḷam varuntip</l>
<l>poṉṉē raṉaiyāy pukuntatu kēḷā</l>
<l>yuṉṉō ṭivvū ruṟṟatoṉ ṟuṇṭukol</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
          
          <l corresp="3"> On the auspicious days during which the Island Propitation [Festival] was performed—</l>
          <l corresp="2"> put on by the protective deity (Campu) for the king of the gods (Indra)</l>
          <l corresp="1"> on the great big island high with/famous for Jaumoon-plum trees
            (Camputtīvu),</l>
          <l corresp="4"> Mātavi and Maṇimēkalai did not come. </l>
          <l corresp="6"> As for Cittirāpati, she suffered affliction and wept.</l>
          <l corresp="5"> Unnabating grief overwhelmed [her] again and again.</l>
          <l corresp="7"> Red-streaks spread across her long eyes. </l>
          <l corresp="8"> She called Vayantamālai, her daughter's confidante, to come, </l>
          <l corresp="9"> and said, 'Tell [my daughter Mātavi] about the gossip [concerning hers and
            Maṇimēkalai's absence from the festival] in the great fertile city!' </l>
<l corresp="10ab">          And Vayantamālai— </l>
<l corresp="13">            after entering the blossom-adorned pavillion </l>
<l corresp="12">            where Mātavi was with Maṇimēkalai, </l>
<l corresp="15">            was sick at heart on seeing the faded body </l>
<l corresp="14">            of the woman with choice jewels and grace when she danced (Mātavi), </l>
<l corresp="11">            because Mātavi had become a wreck, faded in body, dispirited, </l>
<l corresp="10cd">            as a result of renunciation. </l>
<l corresp="16">            [She] said [to her], 'O you who closely resemble Śrī! Listen to what has happened!</l>
<l corresp="17">            Is there any [emnity] towards you that has arisen in the city? </l>
            
            

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
